<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6388&amp;p=68522#p68522"><![CDATA[
Necro because I found this page through a random search for something else, and then I thought of a solution:<br /><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />If you figure out a way, via software, to pre-emptively "guess" when a user is about to physically yank a device off a bus, let me know.  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /><br /></div><br />Strain gauge or similar sensor in the USB port. As the user grabs the plug before removal, the strain gauge sends a signal that the plug is moving in the socket. The OS assumes the user has fingers on the plug and interprets this as a warning of a likely surprise removal in the next split second, so it syncs the file system.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Oct 12, 2010 4:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
